earch tyson foods inc type public traded as nyse tsn sp  component industry food processing founded  headquarters springdale arkansas us key people tom hayes ceo products meat revenue us  billion   us  billion   operating income us  billion   us  billion   net income us  billion   us  million   total assets us  billion   us  billion   total equity us  billion   us  billion   number of employees  subsidiaries hillshire brands website tysonfoodscom tyson foods inc nyse tsn is an american multinational corporation based in springdale arkansas that operates in the food industry the company is the worlds second largest processor and marketer of chicken beef and pork after jbs sa and annually exports the largest percentage of beef out of the united states together with its subsidiaries it operates major food brands including jimmy dean hillshire farm sara lee ball park wright brand aidells and state fair contents  profile  acquisitions  tyson renewable energy  corporate charity  religious activities  corporate governance  board of directors  ceos  controversies  environmental record  employment of undocumented immigrants  price manipulation  undisclosed use of antibiotics  employee abuse  animal abuse  see also  references  external links profileedit the company was established by john w tyson in  and benefitted during world war ii when chicken was not included in foods that were rationed as of  the company employs  people who work at more than  facilities  of which are in the us as of  tyson had about  employees in  states locations are concentrated in the midwest with  locations in arkansas  in texas  in iowa and the remainder of the mostly eastern us with less than  locations tyson also works with  independent contract chicken growerscitation needed it is one of the largest us marketers of valueadded chicken beef and pork to retail grocers broad line foodservice distributors and national fast food and full service restaurant chains fresh beef and pork frozen and fully 